claim: Penal laws (British) which set restrictions on Roman Catholics were removed during the Catholic Emancipation of 19th century.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Catholic emancipation or Catholic relief was a process in the Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland in the late 18th century and early 19th century that involved reducing and removing many of the restrictions on Roman Catholics introduced by the Act of Uniformity , the Test Acts and the penal laws .
